    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "James",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "By governing the tongue, we gain perfection\u2014Heavenly wisdom is pure, peaceable, and full of mercy.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "My brethren, be not many masters, knowing that we shall receive the greater condemnation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0James 3:1 \u2026 strive not for the mastery, knowing that in so doing we shall receive the greater condemnation.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0(also) teachers.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 82:3.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For in many things we offend all. If any man offend not in word, the same is a perfect man, and able also to bridle the whole body.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0stumble, err.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 39:1; Prov. 21:23.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perfection.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1541
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, we put bits in the horses' mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold also the ships, which though they be so great, and are driven of fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the governor listeth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0helmsman, pilot.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast; Rashness.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0forest.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity: so is the tongue among our members, that it defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire of hell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 16:27; Mark 7:20 (19\u201323); Alma 12:14; D&C 88:121.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is tamed, and hath been tamed of mankind:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the tongue can no man tame; it is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip; Profanity.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0untameable, uncontrollable.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therewith bless we God, even the Father; and therewith curse we men, which are made after the similitude of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Out of the same mouth proceedeth blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not so to be.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 12:34; Luke 6:45. TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Doth a fountain send forth at the same place sweet water and bitter?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0spring, well. Moro. 7:11 (6\u201311).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so can no fountain both yield salt water and fresh.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who is a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him shew out of a good conversation his works with meekness of wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 12:13 (13\u201319).",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meek.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against the truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0do not assume superiority over.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This wisdom descendeth not from above, but is earthly, sensual, devilish.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For where envying and strife is, there is confusion and every evil work.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Envy.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, and easy to be entreated, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Intelligence of; Wisdom.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pliant, easily persuaded.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Mercy of.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:42.",
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 171
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace of them that make peace.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace; Peace of God.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peacemakers.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}